Introduction

Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:8000

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by making a POST request to /access_token.

Endpoints

POST register

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"pasyzwszwtxpeqq\",
    \"email\": \"tremayne.kohler@example.net\",
    \"password\": \">?R4Usi|L@vH\",
    \"password_confirmation\": \"olowyuffszfrcsnwwxvxezhebdrxkpiypmuihrdifekzagqzitsslufx\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "pasyzwszwtxpeqq",
    "email": "tremayne.kohler@example.net",
    "password": ">?R4Usi|L@vH",
    "password_confirmation": "olowyuffszfrcsnwwxvxezhebdrxkpiypmuihrdifekzagqzitsslufx"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (201):


{
    "message": "User successfully registered"
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request   

POST register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: pasyzwszwtxpeqq

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: tremayne.kohler@example.net

password   string   

Must be at least 8 characters. Example: >?R4Usi|L@vH

password_confirmation   string   

Must be at least 8 characters. Example: olowyuffszfrcsnwwxvxezhebdrxkpiypmuihrdifekzagqzitsslufx

POST access_token

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/access_token" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"morgan93@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"c~qhvY2Z^@FxLpH>?R4\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/access_token"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "morgan93@example.net",
    "password": "c~qhvY2Z^@FxLpH>?R4"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "message": "Successfully authenticated",
    "token": "1|sz0LJq5iNJ5u5S8BJ5mFuhSSGxHgHLEJsGQ3aokIcdc54ae6"
}

Example response (401):


{
    "message": "Unauthenticated"
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request   

POST access_token

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: morgan93@example.net

password   string   

Must be at least 8 characters. Example: c~qhvY2Z^@FxLpH>?R4

GET v1/stadiums

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/stadiums" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/stadiums"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "data": [
        {
            "id": 108,
            "name": "Adelmar da Costa Carvalho"
        },
        {
            "id": 108,
            "name": "Adelmar da Costa Carvalho"
        }
    ]
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request   

GET v1/stadiums

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

GET v1/stadiums/{id}

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/stadiums/108" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/stadiums/108"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

GET v1/clubs

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/clubs" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/clubs"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
